<h3> Flag Questions for Exams </h3>
<p>From here you can select a course (required), lab (optional), and topic (optional), and see the questions related to those selections.  You can "flag" a question for an exam, which can be used as an incentive for students, like potential bonus marks.</p>
</br>
<%= simple_form_for @result, url: display_flag_questions_path do |f| %>
	<div class = "row">
		<div class = "col-sm-4">
      		<%= f.input :course_id, label: "Select a Course", collection: @courses, include_blank: false %>
    	</div>
    	<div class = "col-sm-4">
      		<%= f.input :lab, label: "Select a lab section", collection: @labs %>
    	</div>
		<div class = "col-sm-4">
      		<%= f.input :name, label: "Select a topic", collection: @topics %>
    	</div>
    </div>
    <%= f.submit "Find Questions", class: "btn btn-medium btn-success" %>
<% end %>